# Cloudflare Pages _redirects.
#
# /assets/* must 404 cleanly when a hashed chunk is missing — otherwise the
# default SPA fallback would rewrite the request to index.html with status
# 200, and the browser would try to evaluate the HTML as a JS module
# ("'text/html' is not a valid JavaScript MIME type"). Listing this rule
# before the SPA catch-all means real assets are still served from disk
# (Pages serves matching static files before consulting _redirects); only
# missing ones fall through to the 404.
/assets/*  /assets/:splat  404

# SPA fallback for client-side routes (React Router).
/*  /index.html  200
